    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Moreover, Uzziah had an host of fighting men,.... A standing army: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that went out to war by bands; to annoy his enemies, and to scour the country from thieves and robbers, that came in troops to plunder: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "according to the number of their account, by the hand of Jeiel the scribe; the secretary of war, who ordered these bands, settled their number, and directed their destination: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and Maaseiah the ruler; or officer over them, a lieutenant: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "under the hand of Hananiah, one of the king's captains; that had the command of them, or at least of one of them. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "under the hand of Hananiah, one of the king's captains; that had the command of them, or at least of one of them. ",
