  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 11.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "That went out to war by bands",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "יוצְאֵי צָבָא לִגְדוּד",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The last of these words occurs thirty-three times, and is rendered \"troop\" ten times, \"company\" four times, \"band\" fourteen times, and (too generically) \"army \"five times. The middle word occurs above four hundred times, is rendered \"host\" an immense preponderance of these times, and probably should have been so rendered without exception. The first word is the pool participle kal of the familiar verb ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "יָצָא",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and compels the translation (given literally),' the goers out of the host by hands.\" Meantime, if the persons here spoken of were ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "leaders, as",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " seems possible, the hiph. participle is required (which would postulate an initial ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "mem",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for the present initial ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "yod",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and a most typical example among some thirty others essentially similar may be quoted from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 40:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Their",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
